rdf:Description.lla:note: Daniel Jones also ship owner. Voyage from Cardiff to Douglas, Carnarvon, Hamburg, South Shields and Plymouth.
Port of leaving is Douglas, Isle of Man. Last ship probably Wiltshire, registered in Newcastle 1882.
Last shi p name could be Sterfoce. Port of joining could be Carnarvon or possibly a German port near Hamburg.
No ship was registered as Miss Peg, there were ships called Miss Pritchard and Miss Beck registered at Caernarfon 1890.
Last ship could be Mariner, registered at Caernarfon 1890 or Marina registered at Limerick 1890.
Port of joining: Shields. Place of birth, possibly 'N Lemer'.
Last ship possibly called Welseley. Port of joining: Shields.
